*'''Current ICU hospitalizations''': 74\n}}\n\n==== April 14 ====\n\nThe Minnesota Department of Health's situation update for 14 April reported the following numbers:<ref name=\"MN Official\" />\n{{plainlist|\n*'''Total approximate number of completed tests''': 39,241\n*'''Approximate number of tests from MDH Public Health Lab''': 9,480\n*'''Approximate number of tests from other labs''': 29,761\n*'''Total positive cases''': 1,695\n*'''Deaths''': 79\n*'''Cases no longer requiring isolation''': 909\n*'''Total active cases''': 707\n*'''Total cases requiring hospitalization''': 405\n*'''Current hospitalizations''': 177\n*'''Current ICU hospitalizations''': 75\n}}\n\n==== April 15 ====\n\nThe Minnesota Department of Health's situation update for 15 April reported the following numbers:<ref name=\"MN Official\" />\n{{plainlist|\n*'''Total approximate number of completed tests''': 40,242\n*'''Approximate number of tests from MDH Public Health Lab''': 9,608\n*'''Approximate number of tests from other labs''': 30,634\n*'''Total positive cases''': 1,809\n*'''Deaths''': 87\n*'''Cases no longer requiring isolation''': 940\n*'''Total active cases''': 782\n*'''Total cases requiring hospitalization''': 445\n*'''Current hospitalizations''': 197\n*'''Current ICU hospitalizations''': 93\n}}\n\n==== April 16 ====\n\nThe Minnesota Department of Health's situation update for 16 April reported the following numbers:<ref name=\"MN Official\" />\n{{plainlist|\n*'''Total approximate number of completed tests''': 41,675\n*'''Approximate number of tests from MDH Public Health Lab''': 9,745\n*'''Approximate number of tests from other labs''': 31,930\n*'''Total positive cases''': 1,912\n*'''Deaths''': 94\n*'''Cases no longer requiring isolation''': 1,020\n*'''Total active cases''': 798\n*'''Total cases requiring hospitalization''': 475\n*'''Current hospitalizations''': 213\n*'''Current ICU hospitalizations''': 103\n}}\n\n==== April 17 ====\n[[File:Liberate Minnesota protest at the Governor's Residence in St Paul, Minnesota (49786738677).jpg|thumb|Protestor at the Governor's Residence in St. Paul]]\nToday, Governor [[Tim Walz]] eased some restrictions on his Stay Home order after receiving pressure from President [[Donald Trump]]<ref>https://twitter.com/realDonaldTrump/status/1251168994066944003</ref> and citizens protesting against the order. He allowed people to engage in various outdoor activities such as hiking, fishing, hunting, and motorboating so long as they maintained a safe and reasonable distance from other people. As well as allowing people to engage in various outdoor activities, he allowed golf courses and bait shops to open.<ref>https://mn.gov/governor/assets/EO%2020-38%20Final_tcm1055-428887.pdf</ref>\n\nThe Minnesota Department of Health's situation update for 17 April reported the following numbers:<ref name=\"MN Official\" />\n{{plainlist|\n*'''Total approximate number of completed tests''': 43,053\n*'''Approximate number of tests from MDH Public Health Lab''': 9,855\n*'''Approximate number of tests from other labs''': 33,198\n*'''Total positive cases''': 2,071\n*'''Deaths''': 111\n*'''Cases no longer requiring isolation''': 1,066\n*'''Total cases requiring hospitalization''': 518\n*'''Current hospitalizations''': 223\n*'''Current ICU hospitalizations''': 106\n}}\n\n==== April 18 ====\n\nThe Minnesota Department of Health's situation update for 18 April reported the following numbers:<ref name=\"MN Official\" />\n{{plainlist|\n*'''Total approximate number of completed tests''': 44,368\n*'''Approximate number of tests from MDH Public Health Lab''': 9,981\n*'''Approximate number of tests from other labs''': 34,387\n*'''Total positive cases''': 2,213\n*'''Deaths''': 121\n*'''Cases no longer requiring isolation''': 1,118\n*'''Total cases requiring hospitalization''': 561\n*'''Current hospitalizations''': 239\n*'''Current ICU hospitalizations''': 111\n}}\n\n==== April 19 ====\n\nThe Minnesota Department of Health's situation update for 19 April reported the following numbers:<ref name=\"MN Official\" />\n{{plainlist|\n*'''Total approximate number of completed tests''': 45,716\n*'''Approximate number of tests from MDH Public Health Lab''': 10,104\n*'''Approximate number of tests from other labs''': 35,612\n*'''Total positive cases''': 2,356\n*'''Deaths''': 134\n*'''Cases no longer requiring isolation''': 1,160\n*'''Total cases requiring hospitalization''': 574\n*'''Current hospitalizations''': 228\n*'''Current ICU hospitalizations''': 116\n}}\n\n==== April 20 ====\n\nThe Minnesota Department of Health's situation update for 20 April reported the following numbers:<ref name=\"MN Official\" />\n{{plainlist|\n*'''Total approximate number of completed tests''': 46,850\n*'''Approximate number of tests from MDH Public Health Lab''': 10,170\n*'''Approximate number of tests from other labs''': 36,680\n*'''Total positive cases''': 2,470\n*'''Deaths''': 143\n*'''Cases no longer requiring isolation''': 1,202\n*'''Total cases requiring hospitalization''': 602\n*'''Current hospitalizations''': 237\n*'''Current ICU hospitalizations''': 126\n}}\n\n==== April 21 ====\n\nThe Minnesota Department of Health's situation update for 20 April reported the following numbers:<ref name=\"MN Official\" />\n{{plainlist|\n*'''Total approximate number of completed tests''': 47,967\n*'''Approximate number of tests from MDH Public Health Lab''': 10,294\n*'''Approximate number of tests from other labs''': 37,407\n*'''Total positive cases''': 2,567\n*'''Deaths''': 160\n*'''Cases no longer requiring isolation''': 1,254\n*'''Total cases requiring hospitalization''': 629\n*'''Current hospitalizations''': 237\n*'''Current ICU hospitalizations''': 117\n}}\n\n== Cases per county ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Cases of COVID-19 per Minnesota County<ref name=\"MN Official\" /><ref name=\"Star Tribune Tracker\">{{cite web|url=https://www.startribune.com/coronavirus-covid-19-minnesota-tracker-map-county-data/568712601/?refresh=true|title=Tracking coronavirus in Minnesota|website=Star Tribune|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref><br>\nCurrent as of 20 April 2020\n!County\n!Total Cases\n!Deaths\n|-\n|[[Aitkin County, Minnesota|Aitkin]]\n|1\n|0\n|-\n|[[Anoka County, Minnesota|Anoka]]\n|95\n|2\n|-\n|[[Becker County, Minnesota|Becker]]\n|1\n|0\n|-\n|[[Beltrami County, Minnesota|Beltrami]]\n|5\n|0\n|-\n|[[Benton County, Minnesota|Benton]]\n|4\n|0\n|-\n|[[Big Stone County, Minnesota|Big Stone]]\n|1\n|0\n|-\n|[[Blue Earth County, Minnesota|Blue Earth]]\n|24\n|0\n|-\n|[[Brown County, Minnesota|Brown]]\n|7\n|1\n|-\n\n|-\n|[[Carlton County, Minnesota|Carlton]]\n|37\n|0\n|-\n|[[Carver County, Minnesota|Carver]]\n|14\n|0\n|-\n|[[Cass County, Minnesota|Cass]]\n|4\n|0\n|-\n|[[Chippewa County, Minnesota|Chippewa]]\n|1\n|0\n|-\n|[[Chisago County, Minnesota|Chisago]]\n|7\n|1\n|-\n|[[Clay County, Minnesota|Clay]]\n|62\n|3\n|-\n|[[Clearwater County, Minnesota|Clearwater]]\n|3\n|0\n|-\n|[[Cottonwood County, Minnesota|Cottonwood]]\n|6\n|0\n|-\n|[[Crow Wing County, Minnesota|Crow Wing]]\n|20\n|0\n|-\n|[[Dakota County, Minnesota|Dakota]]\n|124\n|6\n|-\n|[[Dodge County, Minnesota|Dodge]]\n|18\n|0\n|-\n|[[Douglas County, Minnesota|Douglas]]\n|2\n|0\n|-\n|[[Faribault County, Minnesota|Faribault]]\n|4\n|0\n|-\n|[[Fillmore County, Minnesota|Fillmore]]\n|11\n|0\n|-\n|[[Freeborn County, Minnesota|Freeborn]]\n|33\n|0\n|-\n|[[Goodhue County, Minnesota|Goodhue]]\n|19\n|0\n|-\n|[[Hennepin County, Minnesota|Hennepin]]\n|975\n|80\n|-\n|[[Houston County, Minnesota|Houston]]\n|1\n|0\n|-\n|[[Isanti County, Minnesota|Isanti]]\n|6\n|0\n|-\n|[[Itasca County, Minnesota|Itasca]]\n|2\n|0\n|-\n|[[Jackson County, Minnesota|Jackson]]\n|2\n|0\n|-\n|[[Kandiyohi County, Minnesota|Kandiyohi]]\n|3\n|0\n|-\n|[[Koochiching County, Minnesota|Koochiching]]\n|1\n|0\n|-\n|[[Lac qui Parle County, Minnesota|Lac qui Parle]]\n|1\n|0\n|-\n|[[Le Sueur County, Minnesota|Le Sueur]]\n|22\n|0\n|-\n|[[Lincoln County, Minnesota|Lincoln]]\n|2\n|0\n|-\n|[[Lyon County, Minnesota