->\n\n'''''Memories of Love''''' is the debut studio album by American [[indie pop]] band [[Future Bible Heroes]], released in 1997 in the U.S., the U.K., Europe and Korea.  Its accompanying booklet features twelve word puzzles and games that, if solved correctly, reveal the name of the band and the title of the album, plus the lyrics to each of the album's eleven songs.\n\n== Track listing ==\n{{tracklist\n| all_lyrics      = [[Stephin Merritt]]\n| all_music       = Stephin Merritt (vocal melodies) and Christopher Ewen (music and instrumentation)\n| title1          = Lonely Days\n| length1         = 4:10\n| title2          = She-Devils of the Deep\n| length2         = 4:01\n| title3          = Hopeless\n| length3         = 3:38\n| title4          = Death Opened a Boutique\n| length4         = 3:49\n| title5          = You Pretend to Be the Moon\n| length5         = 4:08\n| title6          = Blond Adonis\n| length6         = 4:49\n| title7          = But You're So Beautiful\n| length7         = 4:13\n| title8          = A You You Never Knew\n| length8         = 2:14\n| title9          = Real Summer\n| length9         = 3:50\n| title10         = Memories of Love\n| length10        = 3:27\n| title11         = You Steal the Scene\n| length11        = 3:45\n}}\n\n== Personnel ==\n;Future Bible Heroes\n* [[Stephin Merritt]] \u2013 vocals\n* [[Claudia Gonson]] \u2013 vocals\n* Christopher Ewen \u2013 instrumentation\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Stephin Merritt}}\n[[Category:1997 debut albums]]\n[[Category:Future Bible Heroes albums]]\n[[Category:Rykodisc albums]]\n\n{{1990s-pop-album-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Holiday56", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Memories_of_Love"}
